<br>
I'm sorry to ask this here,  because its probably been asked many many times.   I'm asking because time is very short right now and I know how helpful the EQ Wizard community is.<br>
<br>
Problem:<br>
<br>
  My good friend and Guildie Wizard has the VS staff, and BG staff.  A friend of hers has the Phinny staff to MQ with her.  They tried to MQ once and Failed. They recieved the Staves back and are going to try again soon.  Is this MQ Broken?  Or possible at all?  It seems so risky i would hate to see them fail,  as you all know how much of a pain the Epic can be.  It shows me how fortunate I was when I completed it.<br>
<br>
If anyone could give some advice from Expierience on how to do this,  it would be most appreciated.   Doing MQ's scare me to death myself,  especially if it were my own epic.<br>
<br>
Thank you Very much!<br>
/bow EQ Wizard community<br>
<br>
Kaelynne Moonshadow<br>
65 Arcanist of Prexus<br>
Shining Alliance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=korteal@graffeswizardcompilation>Korteal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 2:13:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25455.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Question on MQ Epic Staff, need info Advice  </span><hr size=1> Your guildie or her friend prolly doesn't have the required faction to do the turn-in. Tell them both to bring a 3rd person and invis them both while they are in the trade window, but before they do the turn-in thus causing indifferent faction which is required.<br>
<br>
Korteal Zerstorender'Zorn<br>
60 Sorcerer of Prexus<br>
Twilight Avengers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erruinembercore>Erruin Embercore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/19/03 2:43:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25455.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: MQ Epic Staff</span><hr size=1> Have them check their Truespirit faction (the faction all epic quest related npc's you interact with are on) before trying again. An easy way is to go /con Kandin in Butcherblock, or Solomon (sp?) in the temple of Solesek. If they are not at least indifferent, they should really go fix their faction before doing the turn ins.<br>
<br>
There are a few ways I know of to fix this.<br>
<br>
One is to run through the beginning part of the shaman epic a few times. May take some time, but its safe and effective.<br>
<br>
Another, faster, but painful way was added a while back, I believe. It rarely gets used though, because it involves taking a massive hit against Temple of Solesek faction, from killing the Efreet in the back of the temple (the one that gives you negative faction just by hailing him).<br>
Considering the final turn in is actually in the temple, that makes this pretty useless, since you will then need to go kill hundreds of shadowmen to be able to do that last turn in.<br>
I am also not certain they left that option in the game, so I would stick to doing that opener for the shaman epic, or some other method, to raise faction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wizze@graffeswizardcompilation>Wizze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 1:36:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25455.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Temple Faction</span><hr size=1> If you do raise true spirit faction by killing the guy in the temple, you can raise it very very easy by handing money (30 gold or 3 plat) to the merchant in South Ro.  His name is Rathmana Allin and he is all the way in the corner near Oasis zone.  He will take money even if your max KoS, takes about 300plat to get to ally doing this from KoS.  Hope this helps <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deaddragoxo>Deaddragoxo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 1:50:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25455.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Temple Faction</span><hr size=1> doesnt he attack if u have bad faction though? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~christopher.j.bailey/Deadsig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
